    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nFix NVIDIA `convert_layout` lowering for CGA + slice layouts.\r\n\r\nThis removes an overly strict assumption in the optimized swizzling path for shared-memory transfers. The path now only rejects matrix-style load/store lowering when the layout requires a CTA-cluster block offset. Regular shared-memory load/store can carry that offset, so the `CGA + slice` case now lowers correctly instead of hitting an assertion.\r\n\r\n## What changed\r\n\r\n- Relaxed the NVIDIA optimized `convert_layout` lowering so shared-memory load/store can handle CTA-cluster offsets\r\n- Kept `stmatrix/ldmatrix` guarded, since those instructions cannot handle the block-dependent case\r\n- Added a regression test for the reproducer layout:\r\n  - 1D CGA broadcast layout\r\n  - `SliceLayout(0, 2D CGA broadcast layout)`\r\n  - tested with `num_ctas = 2,4,8`\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n- `pytest -s --tb=short python/test/gluon/test_lowerings.py -k convert_1d_to_2d_slice_cga`\r\n\r\n# New contributor declaration\r\n- [x] I am not making a trivial change, such as fixing a typo in a comment.\r\n\r\n- [x] I have written a PR description following these\r\n  [rules](https://cbea.ms/git-commit/#why-not-how).\r\n\r\n- [x] I have run `pre-commit run --from-ref origin/main --to-ref HEAD`.\r\n\r\n- Select one of the following.\r\n  - [ ] I have added tests.\r\n    - `/test` for `lit` tests\r\n    - `/unittest` for C++ tests\r\n    - `/python/test` for end-to-end tests\r\n  - [ ] This PR does not need a test because `FILL THIS IN`.\r\n\r\n- Select one of the following.\r\n  - [ ] I have not added any `lit` tests.\r\n  - [ ] The `lit` tests I have added follow these [best practices](https://mlir.llvm.org/getting_started/TestingGuide/#filecheck-best-practices),\r\n    including the \"tests should be minimal\" section. (Usually running Python code\r\n    and using the instructions it generates is not minimal.)\r\n",
