      "merge_method": "squash",
      "commit_title": "Fix convert_layout lowering for CGA + slice layouts. (#10242)",
      "commit_message": "## Summary\n\nFix NVIDIA `convert_layout` lowering for CGA + slice layouts.\n\nThis removes an overly strict assumption in the optimized swizzling path\nfor shared-memory transfers. The path now only rejects matrix-style\nload/store lowering when the layout requires a CTA-cluster block offset.\nRegular shared-memory load/store can carry that offset, so the `CGA +\nslice` case now lowers correctly instead of hitting an assertion.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Relaxed the NVIDIA optimized `convert_layout` lowering so\nshared-memory load/store can handle CTA-cluster offsets\n- Kept `stmatrix/ldmatrix` guarded, since those instructions cannot\nhandle the block-dependent case\n- Added a regression test for the reproducer layout:\n  - 1D CGA broadcast layout\n  - `SliceLayout(0, 2D CGA broadcast layout)`\n  - tested with `num_ctas = 2,4,8`\n\n## Validation\n- `pytest -s --tb=short python/test/gluon/test_lowerings.py -k\nconvert_1d_to_2d_slice_cga`\n\n# New contributor declaration\n- [x] I am not making a trivial change, such as fixing a typo in a\ncomment.\n\n- [x] I have written a PR description following these\n  [rules](https://cbea.ms/git-commit/#why-not-how).\n\n- [x] I have run `pre-commit run --from-ref origin/main --to-ref HEAD`.\n\n- Select one of the following.\n  - [ ] I have added tests.\n    - `/test` for `lit` tests\n    - `/unittest` for C++ tests\n    - `/python/test` for end-to-end tests\n  - [ ] This PR does not need a test because `FILL THIS IN`.\n\n- Select one of the following.\n  - [ ] I have not added any `lit` tests.\n- [ ] The `lit` tests I have added follow these [best\npractices](https://mlir.llvm.org/getting_started/TestingGuide/#filecheck-best-practices),\nincluding the \"tests should be minimal\" section. (Usually running Python\ncode\n    and using the instructions it generates is not minimal.)"
